text = "[b][color=3C1006]GoCars - Python Programming Guide[/color][/b]

[b]How to Play:[/b]
Write Python code to control vehicles and complete levels. Your code runs on all spawned cars automatically!

[b][color=8c6245]═══ Car Commands ═══[/color][/b]

[b]Movement:[/b]
  [color=aa7959]car.go()[/color]           - Start moving forward
  [color=aa7959]car.stop()[/color]         - Stop immediately
  [color=aa7959]car.turn(\"left\")[/color]   - Turn 90° left
  [color=aa7959]car.turn(\"right\")[/color]  - Turn 90° right

[b]Road Detection:[/b]
  [color=aa7959]car.front_road()[/color]   - Road ahead? → True/False
  [color=aa7959]car.left_road()[/color]    - Road to left? → True/False
  [color=aa7959]car.right_road()[/color]   - Road to right? → True/False

[b]Obstacle Detection:[/b]
  [color=aa7959]car.front_car()[/color]    - Any car ahead? → True/False
  [color=aa7959]car.front_crash()[/color]  - Crashed car ahead? → True/False

[b]State Queries:[/b]
  [color=aa7959]car.at_end()[/color]       - At destination? → True/False
  [color=aa7959]car.at_cross()[/color]     - At intersection? → True/False
  [color=aa7959]car.at_red()[/color]       - Near red light? → True/False


[b][color=8c6245]═══ Stoplight Commands ═══[/color][/b]

[b]Control:[/b]
  [color=aa7959]stoplight.red()[/color]    - Set to red
  [color=aa7959]stoplight.green()[/color]  - Set to green

[b]State:[/b]
  [color=aa7959]stoplight.is_red()[/color]    - Is red? → True/False
  [color=aa7959]stoplight.is_green()[/color]  - Is green? → True/False


[b][color=8c6245]═══ Python Syntax ═══[/color][/b]

[b][color=8c6245]If Statements:[/color][/b]
  if car.front_road():
      car.go()
  elif car.left_road():
	  car.turn(\"left\")
  else:
      car.stop()

[b]While Loops:[/b]
  while not car.at_end():
      if car.front_road():
          car.go()

[b]Functions:[/b]
  def smart_turn(direction):
      car.turn(direction)
      car.go()

  smart_turn(\"left\")


[b][color=8c6245]═══ Import System ═══[/color][/b]
Create helper modules to organize your code:

[b][color=8c6245]1. Create a module file (helpers.py):[/color][/b]
  
def avoid_crash():
      if car.front_crash():
          if car.left_road():
			  car.turn(\"left\")
          elif car.right_road()
			  car.turn(\"right\")

  def navigate():
      if car.front_road():
          car.go()
      else:
          car.stop()

[b][color=8c6245]2. Import functions in main.py:[/color][/b]
  from helpers import avoid_crash, navigate

  while not car.at_end():
      avoid_crash()
      navigate()[/color]

[b][color=8c6245]3. Nested modules:[/color][/b]
  from modules.navigation import find_path


[b][color=8c6245]═══ Tips & Tricks ═══[/color][/b]

• [color=8c6245]Red lights don't auto-stop![/color] You must check stoplight state
• [color=8c6245]Crashed cars stay on map[/color] as obstacles - navigate around them
• [color=8c6245]Your code runs on ALL cars[/color] - make it handle multiple scenarios
• [color=8c6245]Use functions[/color] to break complex logic into reusable pieces
• [color=8c6245]Organize with modules[/color] for cleaner, more maintainable code
• [color=8c6245]Test edge cases:[/color] dead ends, multiple obstacles, timing


[b][color=8c6245]═══ Example: Complete Solution ═══[/color][/b]

def check_stoplight():
    if stoplight.is_red():
        car.stop()
        return False
    return True

def navigate_safely():
    if car.front_crash():
        if car.left_road():
			car.turn(\"left\")
        elif car.right_road():
			car.turn(\"right\")
        else:
            car.stop()
    elif car.front_road() and check_stoplight():
        car.go()
    elif car.left_road():
		car.turn(\"left\")
    elif car.right_road():
		car.turn(\"right\")
    else:
        car.stop()

while not car.at_end():
    navigate_safely()


